<h2>Walking Forward Looking Back</h2>
<div class="tale">
	<h5>By: Solf</h5>
	<div class="text">
		Walking forward looking back<br />
By Solf<br />
<br />
I walk these roads.<br />
<br />
My pack loaded on my back.<br />
<br />
My staff aids my step, as I scan the horizon for signs of danger.<br />
<br />
Strange how the mind can wander with such a mundane task as a long walk.<br />
<br />
Voices come and go as my eyes glaze over, entering a state of daydream while I remain cognizant enough to continue my journey.<br />
<br />
Voices from the past... from different worlds, long ago.<br />
<br />
A man named Brimstone, and Freejack.<br />
<br />
Lochedahnan and Akira... A Keep... my home.<br />
<br />
A clearing... buildings... Santiago, Stubby, Broog, Deathwish Dragon.<br />
<br />
Brewman, Hawkeye, Brigadier, and Kelsam.<br />
<br />
Names and voices of the past come and go, washing over me like a cleansing rain.<br />
<br />
Another world, another time... a more recent past.<br />
<br />
There's a marble city... and more voices... images.<br />
<br />
Aanlain and Azlana.<br />
<br />
Bagulan, Argil, and Waran...<br />
<br />
Penaden, and Wryliak...<br />
<br />
More voices of friends from long ago.<br />
<br />
Too many to focus on.<br />
<br />
With a start, I realize that I had not been paying attention to my steps, lost in the past.<br />
<br />
I bring myself back to the present and focus on those I now call my friends.<br />
<br />
Some have made the journeys with me from world to world.<br />
<br />
Some are new... I can hear their voices as well.<br />
<br />
Enosh, Joxer, and Orion.<br />
<br />
Tasslehof, Kileyan, and Gwenn.<br />
<br />
I smile to myself as I approach my destination: The hamlet of Hebian-To, my home for now.<br />
<br />
I feel very fortunate to have had such an existence, moving from world to world.<br />
<br />
My life feels endless, and those I have called my friends have helped to shape who I am.<br />
<br />
Some call me reclusive, or mysterious.<br />
<br />
I have been called a lunatic, and a prophet.<br />
<br />
I have been known as a savior and as a doombringer.<br />
<br />
I have had many names, some I've already forgotten.<br />
<br />
Now they just call me the Solf.<br />
<br />
Less of a name, more of a word.<br />
<br />
A word meaning what I have become over the years and through the worlds.<br />
<br />
Perhaps I am Warped, a bit jaded from all I have seen and done.<br />
<br />
I like to think I am enlightened, educated, and better prepared for the next turn in the road.<br />
<br />
I suppose it is who you ask, my friends or my enemies, as to what is the meaning of my name.<br />
<br />
I enter the center of town, and the locals avoid me like the plague.<br />
<br />
They do not even know me, but they can tell that I am different.<br />
<br />
Different for better or worse, I do not know, but I continue as I always have.<br />
<br />
Waiting for the next fork in the road, I will do what I can in this world.<br />
<br />
I will move forward, and I will succeed, knowing that I shall always have my brothers and sisters by my side.<br />
<br />
I bow my head and silently thank all my friends, for helping to mold me into what I have become.<br />
<br />
My friends, brothers, and sisters. Past, present, and future.<br />
<br />
I look forward to see what the future holds.<br />
<br />
It is good to be me.<br />
<br />
-The Solf-
	</div>
